@full_implementation
title: Full Implementation
on-arrival: budget -= 3; reformer_approval += 4; moderate_approval += 1; hardliner_approval -= 4; popular_approval -= 3

We enforce *Gospriemka* rigorously, rejecting all substandard goods and ensuring strict adherence to quality standards. This is a bold step toward modernization but leads to severe shortages and industrial disruptions, hurting the economy.

@controlled_rollout
title: Controlled Rollout
on-arrival: budget -= 2; reformer_approval += 2; moderate_approval += 2; hardliner_approval -= 2; popular_approval -= 1

We phase in *Gospriemka* gradually, allowing enterprises time to adjust while maintaining some production flexibility. Production still falls and quality improvement is slowed, but this softens the economic impact.

@abandon_gospriemka
title: Abandon Gospriemka
on-arrival: budget += 2; reformer_approval -= 3; hardliner_approval += 2

We scrap *Gospriemka*, maintaining the current system of quantity-based production. This prevents supply chain disruptions but allows the production of poor-quality goods to continue, frustrating consumers.